# Commit discipline

## ASCII-only commit messages

Cloudflare Pages deployments API rejects non-ASCII commit messages. The asset upload succeeds, but the deployment-record creation fails with `[code: 8000111] Invalid commit message, it must be a valid UTF-8 string` if the message contains:

- Em-dashes (U+2014) - use straight hyphens instead
- Curly quotes (smart punctuation U+2018-201D) - use straight quotes
- Sparkles, emoji, any non-ASCII characters

Compose every commit message in plain ASCII from the start. If a non-ASCII message slips through, the fix is `git commit --amend -m "<plain ASCII>"` + `git push --force-with-lease`.

## One commit per change, never two within ~10 seconds

CF Pages dedups the second commit if two land within ~10 seconds. If a follow-up tweak is needed, wait at least 15 seconds OR squash into a single commit before pushing.

## Conventional commit prefixes

Use `fix:`, `feat:`, `chore:`, `polish:`, `docs:` as prefixes when reasonable. Keeps git log scannable.
